      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
      "body" : "I actually used this solution, but I wouldn&#39;t advise this. As the documentation on TreeSet states (see <a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/javase/1.4.2/docs/api/java/util/TreeSet.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">download.oracle.com/javase/1.4.2/docs/api/java/util/&hellip;</a>), it effectively uses the compareTo() method instead of the equals() method - so if you have two objects in the set that have the same equals() outcome, they will be seen as duplicates and, as such, will not be added to the TreeSet. Beware."
