    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>The answer <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/740299/how-do-i-sort-a-set-in-java/740301#740301\">provided by the OP</a> is not the best. It is inefficient, as it creates a new <code>List</code> <em>and</em> an unnecessary new array. Also, it raises \"unchecked\" warnings because of the type safety issues around generic arrays.</p>\n\n<p>Instead, use something like this: </p>\n\n<pre><code>public static\n&lt;T extends Comparable&lt;? super T&gt;&gt; List&lt;T&gt; asSortedList(Collection&lt;T&gt; c) {\n  List&lt;T&gt; list = new ArrayList&lt;T&gt;(c);\n  java.util.Collections.sort(list);\n  return list;\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Here's a usage example:</p>\n\n<pre><code>Map&lt;Integer, String&gt; map = new HashMap&lt;Integer, String&gt;();\n/* Add entries to the map. */\n...\n/* Now get a sorted list of the *values* in the map. */\nCollection&lt;String&gt; unsorted = map.values();\nList&lt;String&gt; sorted = Util.asSortedList(unsorted);\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 622336,
      "reputation" : 75,
      "user_id" : 364240,
      "user_type" : "unregistered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/bc36bf6d72808007c83157bc6988b63d?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Amit",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/364240/amit"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1318878950,
    "last_edit_date" : 1318878950,
    "creation_date" : 1276235484,
    "answer_id" : 3020477,
    "question_id" : 740299,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can convert a set into an <code>ArrayList</code>, where you can sort the <code>ArrayList</code> using <code>Collections.sort(List)</code>.</p>\n\n<p>Here is the code:</p>\n\n<pre><code>keySet = (Set) map.keySet();\nArrayList list = new ArrayList(keySet);     \nCollections.sort(list);\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 431486,
      "reputation" : 3709,
      "user_id" : 815566,
      "user_type" : "registered",
